  Dialogue:
  - Were you treated well?
  - I didn't know drug dealers were so kind when carrying out kidnappings, this cell
    is very comfortable and the food was delicious.
  - Did you like? I prepared it myself.
  - Really?
  - "Yes, my favorite hobby is cooking because I remember my late wife teaching me\u2026
    those are good memories."
  - But that no longer matters.
  - We drug dealers aren't kind, but we have a motto.
  - "Endless love for our family\u2026"
  - "\u2026and endless hatred for our enemies"
  - Exactly, William Ulbricht is my real enemy, I kidnapped you just so he would
    agree to duel with me.
  - However the Assassins Guild is not my enemy and I do not wish the enmity of Belmont
    Ebu. Will you accept my apology for arresting you?
  - It's okay, after all we're all arrested.
  - It wasn't ok for Maduin, after all he feared that William would die in the duel,
    but he ignored this because he wanted to talk about the path of enlightenment.
  - Whenever he could, he tried to appear wise in displaying his reflections on this
    topic.
  - What do you mean?
  - We are tied to the concept of wealth, glory and power. We pursue it all the time
    thinking that we will achieve peace and happiness in this way.
  - Joshua, you are a man who has achieved everything people want. Despite growing
    up in poverty, you ended up building an empire.
  - Did the money and power you gained bring you peace or did it just make you more
    thirsty for new conquests?
  - I have a comfortable life today and am proud of the empire I've built.
  - But I think I understand what you mean, young man, I was never satisfied with
    my accomplishments, instead I just sought to reach even higher goals.
  - I only realized everything I had when I lost it.
  - I wish I had spent more time with Harold.
  - I'm sorry for your loss.
  - "How did that Shuana poetry say? \u201CAn enlightened man appreciates the music
    of the universe and the silence of his own soul.\u201D Do you know what that
    means?"
  - If I'm not mistaken, it means that happiness is in accepting who you are and
    the world around you.
  - How could I accept this world after my son died? How could I accept who I am
    after wasting so many moments I could have with him?
  - I don't know.
  DialogueBR:
  - "Voc\xEA foi bem tratado?"
  - "N\xE3o sabia que traficantes eram t\xE3o gentis quando realizavam sequestros,
    essa cela \xE9 bem confort\xE1vel e a comida estava deliciosa.\r\n"
  - "Voc\xEA gostou? Eu mesmo que preparei."
  - Jura?
  - "Sim, meu passatempo preferido \xE9 cozinhar porque eu me lembro da minha falecida
    esposa me ensinando\u2026 s\xE3o boas mem\xF3rias."
  - "Mas isso j\xE1 n\xE3o importa."
  - "N\xF3s traficantes n\xE3o somos gentis, mas n\xF3s temos um lema."
  - "Amor infinito para a nossa fam\xEDlia\u2026"
  - "\u2026e \xF3dio infinito para os nossos inimigos."
  - "Exatamente, William Ulbricht \xE9 meu verdadeiro inimigo, eu te sequestrei apenas
    para que ele aceitasse duelar comigo.\r"
  - "Entretanto a Guilda de Assassinos n\xE3o \xE9 minha inimiga e eu n\xE3o desejo
    a inimizade da Belmont Ebu. Voc\xEA aceita meu pedido de desculpas por te prender?\r"
  - "Est\xE1 tudo bem, afinal todos estamos presos."
  - "N\xE3o estava tudo bem para Maduin, afinal ele temia que William morresse no
    duelo, mas ele ignorou isso porque queria discursar sobre o caminho da ilumina\xE7\xE3o. "
  - "Sempre que podia, ele tentava parecer s\xE1bio ao exibir suas reflex\xF5es sobre
    esse tema.\r\n"
  - "Como assim?\r"
  - "N\xF3s estamos presos ao conceito de riqueza, gl\xF3ria e poder. N\xF3s buscamos
    isso o tempo todo achando que alcan\xE7aremos a paz e a felicidade dessa forma.\r\n"
  - "Joshua, voc\xEA \xE9 um homem que conseguiu tudo aquilo que as pessoas almejam.
    Apesar de ter crescido na pobreza, voc\xEA acabou construindo um imp\xE9rio."
  - "O dinheiro e o poder que voc\xEA conquistou te trouxe paz ou apenas te deixou
    mais sedento por novas conquistas?\r"
  - "Eu tenho uma vida confort\xE1vel hoje e me orgulho do imp\xE9rio que constru\xED.\r\n"
  - "Mas acho que entendo o que voc\xEA quer dizer, jovem, eu nunca fiquei satisfeito
    com minhas realiza\xE7\xF5es, ao inv\xE9s disso eu apenas busquei atingir metas
    ainda mais elevadas.\r\n"
  - "Eu s\xF3 percebi tudo o que eu tinha quando perdi."
  - Eu queria ter passado mais tempo com o Harold.
  - "Sinto muito por sua perda.\r"
  - "Como que aquela poesia shuana dizia? \u201CUm homem iluminado aprecia a m\xFAsica
    do universo e o sil\xEAncio da pr\xF3pria alma\u201D. Voc\xEA sabe o que isso
    significa?"
  - "Como eu poderia aceitar este mundo ap\xF3s meu filho morrer? Como eu poderia
    aceitar quem eu sou ap\xF3s ter desperdi\xE7ado tantos momentos que eu poderia
    ter com ele?\r"
  - "Eu n\xE3o sei."
  - "Joshua come\xE7ou a chorar."
